{"title_page": "Easy Rider (band)", "text_new": "{{AFC submission|t||ts=20200416111527|u=BenBarek1903|ns=118}}\n{{other uses|Easy Rider (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=Apr 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Easy Rider\n| image           = \n| caption         = | image_size      = \n| landscape       = \n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = [[Madrid]], [[Spain]]\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Power metal]]\n* [[Progressive metal]]\n* [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]]\n}}\n| years_active    = 1988\u2013present \n| label           = {{flatlist|\n* [[SOHO Music]]\n* [[Locomotive Music]]\n* [[Krea Film Producciones]]\n}}\n| website         = {{URL| http://easy-rider.es/home.html\n }}\n| current_members = \n* Javier Villanueva\n* Daniel Castellanos\n* Jos\u00e9 A. Villanueva\n* Rafa D\u00edaz\n* Ron Finn\n| past_members    = \n* Eugenio Gara\u00f1eda\n* Antonio M. Chaves\n}}\n\nEasy Rider is a [[Spain|Spanish]] [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] band from [[Madrid]]. They reached particular success in the Spanish [[power metal]] and [[progressive metal]] scene by the end of the 1990s and beginning of the 2000s.\n\n==History==\n\nTheir first album hit the market in 1997 under the title ''Perfecta Creaci\u00f3n'', composed of 9 songs in [[English language|English]] and [[Spanish language|Spanish]]. The album was received well by the music media. Between June and September of 1998 Easy Rider recorded their second album ''Lord of the Storm''. This album was sung entirely in English with its sights set on the international market. Those two albums led them to win in 1999 the \"Best New Band Award\" from the prestigious Spanish music magazine [[:es:Vicente_Romero_\"Mariscal\"|Heavy Rock]]. Their third album, that led them to the peak of their popularity and is considered their best by the fans, ''Evilution'' (with lyrics literally extracted from the [[Book of Revelation]]), was released in 2000 with a great impact among the specialized press in [[Europe]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metalcry.com/discos/easy-rider-evilution/|title=EASY RIDER \u2013 EVILUTION \u2013 Metalcry.com :: Tu Web de Rock y Metal|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rafabasa.com/2000/10/31/easy-rider-evilution-octubre-2000/|title=EASY RIDER \u2013 Evilution \u2013 Octubre 2000 {{!}} WWW.RAFABASA.COM - Noticias en espa\u00f1ol sobre el heavy metal y los grupos de heavy metal.|last=admin|date=2000-10-31|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://easy-rider.es/bio/english.html|title=Easy Rider Official Website\\BIOGRAPHY|website=easy-rider.es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, the singer Eugenio Gara\u00f1eda left the band together with the drummer Antonio Chaves. He was replaced by the [[United States|american]] Ron Finn, who had just been finally rejected to succeed [[Jon Oliva]] as the new singer of [[Savatage]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ronfinnmusic.com/about-ron|title=Ron Finn - About Ron -|website=ronfinnmusic.com|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://corsariosdelmetal.blogspot.com/2014/10/presentacion-del-nuevo-disco-de-easy.html|title=Corsarios del Metal. Portal de Heavy Metal en Castellano. Radio en Directo y Podcast|last=corsariosdelmetal.blogspot.com|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> Although their popularity declined, their last album, ''From the Darkness'', was selected as one of the ten best Spanish hard rock/metal albums of 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mariskalrock.com/secciones/volumen_brutal/easy-rider-comprometidos-con-el-heavy-metal/|title=Easy Rider, compromised with Heavy Metal|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nEasy Rider has shared the stage with renowned bands like [[Yngwie Malmsteen|Yngwie J. Malmsteen]], [[Blind Guardian]], [[Gamma ray|Gamma Ray]], [[Stratovarius]] or [[Manowar]] and made several tours throughout their Spanish territory. In 2004 they embarked on a tour of 15 dates across Europe. During their career, the band has also participated in numerous festivals throughout Spain, such as Eurometal 99, 2000, Metal Machina 2000, Vi\u00f1arock 2003, Legends of Rock 2010, HOM Festival 2014 or Legends of Rock 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://redhardnheavy.com/cronica-del-concierto-de-easy-rider-presentando-from-the-darkness-en-madrid/|title=Easy Rider, From the Darkness|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Band members==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n'''Current members'''\n* Ron Finn - lead vocals (2001\u2013present)</small>\n* Javier Villanueva - guitar (1988-present)</small>\n* Daniel Castellanos - guitar (1988-present)</small>\n* Jos\u00e9 A. Villanueva - bass (1988-present)</small> \n* Rafa D\u00edaz - drums (2001-present)</small>\n\n{{col-2}}\n\n'''Former members'''\n*Eugenio Gara\u00f1eda- lead vocals <small>(1996\u20132001)</small>\n*Antonio M. Chaves- drums <small>(1996\u20132001, 2014)</small>\n{{col-end}}\n\n\n==Discography==\n'''Studio albums'''\n*''Perfecta Creaci\u00f3n'' (1997)\n*''Lord of the Storm'' (1998)\n*''Evilution'' (2000)\n*''Regeneration'' (2002)\n*''Animal'' (2003)\n*''From the Darkness'' (2014)\n\n==See also ==\n*[[List of power metal bands]]\n\n{{AFC submission|||ts=20200416115414|u=BenBarek1903|ns=118}}\n", "text_old": "{{Db-r2}}\n#REDIRECT [[Draft:Easy Rider (band)]]\n\n{{Redirect category shell|\n{{R from move}}\n}}\n", "name_user": "BenBarek1903", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Easy_Rider_(band)"}
